      "name": "Relative hemolysis index bench-test comparison",
      "description": "Predicted normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro bench test data from three independent laboratories. Predicted NIH within ±15% of measured mean across all five operating points. Acceptance criterion (RH < 1 versus predicate) met at all conditions."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/mesh-convergence-study",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence and discretisation error quantification",
      "description": "Richardson extrapolation performed on three systematically refined meshes (4.2 M, 12.1 M, 31.8 M elements). Grid convergence index below 2.3% for NIH at all operating points. Selected production mesh (12.1 M elements) achieves adequate accuracy with acceptable computational cost."
    }
  ],
