      "rationale": "PIV experiments used the FDA generic pump geometry with a blood-analogue fluid (glycerol–water, matched viscosity). Hemolysis bench tests used bovine blood at matched viscosity and haematocrit. Operating points span the COU flow-speed envelope. Minor geometric differences (optical access windows) documented and assessed as negligible for bulk flow metrics. Validation relevance level 2 is achieved."
    },
